.TH ecd-convert 1  "convert " 
.SH NAME
ecd\-convert \- Convert file encoding
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBecd convert\fR [\fB\-\-color\fR] <\fB\-f\fR|\fB\-\-file\fR> <\fB\-\-from\fR> <\fB\-\-to\fR> [\fB\-o\fR|\fB\-\-output\fR] [\fB\-\-strict\fR] [\fB\-\-bom\fR] [\fB\-\-force\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Convert file encoding
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-color\fR \fI<WHEN>\fR [default: never]
When to colorize encoding labels (`[UTF\-8]`, `[SKIP]`, …) in batch output
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
auto: Colorize when stdout is a terminal and `NO_COLOR` is unset
.IP \(bu 2
never: Never colorize (default)
.IP \(bu 2
always: Always colorize (ANSI escapes; useful for piping to `less \-R`)
.RE
.TP
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-file\fR \fI<PATH>\fR
File to convert
.TP
\fB\-\-from\fR \fI<ENC>\fR
